Can be tested with the following diff:

```diff
diff --git a/src/index/base.cpp b/src/index/base.cpp
index 955d7b67c9..9811074a2c 100644
--- a/src/index/base.cpp
+++ b/src/index/base.cpp
@@ -179,7 +179,7 @@ void BaseIndex::Sync()
                 }
             }
             if (pindex_next->pprev != pindex && !Rewind(pindex, pindex_next->pprev)) {
-                FatalErrorf("%s: Failed to rewind index %s to a previous chain tip", __func__, GetName());
+                FatalErrorf("%s: /* Failed to rewind index %s to a previous chain tip */", __func__, GetName());
                 return;
             }
             pindex = pindex_next;
```

On master (fails):

```
$ ./test/lint/lint-format-strings.py 
src/index/base.cpp: Expected 1 argument(s) after format string but found 2 argument(s): FatalErrorf("%s: ", __func__, GetName())
```

On this pull (compilation check passes correctly).

